In the poetry of all lands lovers have appealed to birds to be their
messengers to the distant loved one. This is so common in Indian poetry
as to have become a recognised convention. Here the saint sends his
message of love and devotion, in one case by a humming bee, in the other
by the Indian cuckoo, to Śiva who dwells in Tillai, i.e. Chidambaram.

<span id="page_108">p. 108</span> <span id="page_109">p. 109</span>

