One of the little childishnesses involved in idolatry is that every
morning with solemn ceremony the idol must be wakened from his sleep,
bathed, and dressed. Here is a song with which he is roused from
slumber. But notice how successfully our author has filled his poem with
the fresh morning feeling, and the sights and sounds of the sudden break
of the Indian dawn.

